<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFE8015463A5F5AE914C8C27" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFE8015463A5F5AE914C8C27" blockId="10.[151,760,1454,1797]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFE8015463A5F5AE92688EE7" bold="true" box="[151,281,1454,1477]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFE801546213F5AE92DA8EE7" author="BALY J. S." box="[289,427,1454,1477]" firstAuthor="BALY" journalOrPublisher="Annals and Magazine of Natural History" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" pagination="108 - 120" part="4" refId="ref30309" refString="BALY J. S. 1879 a: Descriptions of new genera and species of Gallerucinae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 5 th Series 4: 108 - 120." title="Descriptions of new genera and species of Gallerucinae" type="journal article" year="1879" yearSuffix="a">BALY (1879a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFE80154628AF5AE928B8EE7" author="BALY J. S." box="[440,506,1454,1477]" firstAuthor="BALY" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Entomological Society of London" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" pagination="27 - 39" part="1886" refId="ref30387" refString="BALY J. S. 1886 a: Descriptions of new genera and species of Galerucidae. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1886: 27 - 39." title="Descriptions of new genera and species of Galerucidae" type="journal article" year="1886" yearSuffix="a">1886a</bibRefCitation>
) published the descriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFE8015463C6F5CE92978EC7" box="[244,486,1486,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oedicerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicipennis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFE8015463C6F5CE92978EC7" box="[244,486,1486,1509]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Oedicerus apicipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFE80154612DF5CE91808EC7" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1886" box="[543,753,1486,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Nacrea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicipennis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFE80154612DF5CE91808EC7" box="[543,753,1486,1509]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Nacrea apicipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Only the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFE801546236F5EE92158D27" box="[260,356,1518,1541]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFE8015462BDF5EE91168D27" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1886" box="[399,615,1518,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Nacrea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicipennis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFE8015462BDF5EE91168D27" box="[399,615,1518,1541]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Nacrea apicipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is deposited in the BMNH (
<figureCitation id="1CDC43CDFFE801546276F60E92E88D07" box="[324,409,1550,1573]" captionStart="Figs 64–73" captionStartId="17.[151,188,1932,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1440,193,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-14@17.[155,1441,193,1849]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 64–73. Habitus of Taumacera. 64– T. musaamani (Mohamedsaid, 2010) (male); 65 – T. cervicornis (Baly, 1861) (male); 66 – T. lewisi (Jacoby, 1887) (male); 67 – T. lewisi(female, holotype of Aenidea hirtipennis Jacoby, 1887); 68 – T. mirabilis (Jacoby, 1887) (male, holotype); 69 – T. unicolor (Jacoby, 1887) (male, holotype); 72 – T. costatipennis (Jacoby, 1896) (male, syntype); 71 – T. deusta Thunberg, 1814 (male, holotype); 72 – T. deusta (male, holotype of Nacrea apicipennis Baly, 1886); 73 – T. fulvicollis (Jacoby, 1881) (female, syntype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505534" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505534/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
). Based on comparison of both Balyʼs descriptions I speculate that they refer to the same specimen as the texts in Latin are nearly the same and in both descriptions only one specimen with five broken apical antennomeres is mentioned. Therefore the names are objective synonyms as 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFE8015462F1F6AE91278DE7" author="BALY J. S." box="[451,598,1710,1733]" firstAuthor="BALY" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Entomological Society of London" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" pagination="27 - 39" part="1886" refId="ref30387" refString="BALY J. S. 1886 a: Descriptions of new genera and species of Galerucidae. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1886: 27 - 39." title="Descriptions of new genera and species of Galerucidae" type="journal article" year="1886" yearSuffix="a">BALY (1886a)</bibRefCitation>
probably only repeated the description and put a new identification label when proposing the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFE8015462DAF6EE91478C27" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1886" box="[488,566,1774,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Nacrea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFE8015462DAF6EE91478C27" box="[488,566,1774,1797]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Nacrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
